{
  "texts": [
    "It comprises two elements: an adaptable one, chosen by the teacher or researcher, which requests a specific output (e.g., \"encourage the student to.",
    "\"), and an adaptive one, selected by the LLM, that is customized to the unique aspects of the student's answer (e.g., \".",
    "the concepts that they misunderstood or that were missing\").",
    "In this way, the LLM is supposed to follow principles that are known from cognitive theory and prior educational research.",
    "The principles specifically incorporated here pertain to formative feedback and SRL (see Section II)."
  ]
}